title: Ghana heads to the polls amid deepening economic crisis
description: Once one of Africa’s economic powerhouses, Ghana has struggled with a cost-of-living crisis and high inflationMillions of Ghanaians have headed to the polls in a presidential election after a campaign dominated by what many see as the west African country’s worst economic crisis in a generation.Polls opened at 7am and will close at 5pm, with early results expected late on Saturday. The first official results will be released by Tuesday. Continue reading...
author: Eromo Egbejule in Abidjan and Caleb Ahinakwah in Accra

title: Namibia elects its first female president in disputed elections
description: Vice-president Netumbo Nandi-Ndaitwah avoids runoff vote, as win extends Swapo party’s 34-year hold on powerNamibia has elected its first female leader, with Netumbo Nandi-Ndaitwah declared the winner of last week’s presidential election in a result that will extend the ruling Swapo party’s 34-year hold on power.Nandi-Ndaitwah, the current vice-president, won with 57% of the vote, according to official results, defying predictions that she might be forced into a runoff. Swapo has ruled the country since its independence from apartheid South Africa in 1990. Continue reading...
author: Rachel Savage and agencies in Windhoek

title: 'Buy a suit Zelenskyy': Ukrainian president greets Trump in casual sweatshirt and boots
description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy's casual attire during meetings with US President-elect Donald Trump and French President Emmanuel Macron in Paris sparked online debate. While some criticized his choice of clothing, others, including Senator John Fetterman, expressed support.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Brian Thompson murder case: NYPD divers search lake for murder weapon as manhunt enters fourth day
description: NYPD divers searched Central Park's lake for the murder weapon used in the assassination of UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson. A backpack belonging to the suspect was found, but the weapon and electric bicycle remain missing. Investigators believe the suspect, who arrived from Atlanta, has fled the city by bus. A $60,000 reward is offered for information leading to an arrest.
author: TOI World Desk
